    "#### 4. The battle starts! Using the variables you've created above, code the execution of spell clashes. Remember that a sorcerer wins if he succeeds in winning 3 spell clashes in a row. \n",
    "If a clash ends up in a tie, the counter of wins in a row is not restarted to 0. Remember to print who is the winner of the battle. "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Gandalf wins!\n",
      "0 3\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "for spell in zip(gandalf, saruman):\n",
    "    if spell[0] > spell[1]:\n",
    "        gandalf_wins += 1\n",
    "        saruman_wins = 0\n",
    "        if gandalf_wins == 3:\n",
    "            print(\"Gandalf wins!\")\n",
    "    else:\n",
    "        saruman_wins += 1\n",
    "        gandalf_wins = 0\n",
    "        if saruman_wins == 3:\n",
    "            print(\"Saruman wins!\")\n",
    "print(saruman_wins,gandalf_wins )"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "#### 5. Find the average spell power of Gandalf and Saruman. "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 12,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "18.4 26.2\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "spell_power_gandalf = sum(gandalf) / len(gandalf)\n",
    "spell_power_saruman = sum(saruman) / len(saruman)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(spell_power_gandalf, spell_power_saruman)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "#### 6. Find the standard deviation of the spell power of Gandalf and Saruman. "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 28,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "(4.329780281177467e-17+0.7071067811865476j) (1.9363366072701937e-17+0.31622776601683794j)\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "squared_result_gandalf = []\n",
    "squared_result_saruman = []\n",
    "\n",
    "for spell in gandalf:\n",
    "    result = float(int((spell - spell_power_gandalf))^2)\n",
    "    squared_result_gandalf.append(result)\n",
    "    gandalf_variance = (1 / len(gandalf)) * sum(squared_result_gandalf)\n",
    "    standard_dev_gandalf = gandalf_variance**(1/2)\n",
    "    \n",
    "for spell in saruman:\n",
    "    result = float(int((spell - spell_power_saruman))^2)\n",
    "    squared_result_saruman.append(result)\n",
    "    saruman_variance = (1 / len(saruman)) * sum(squared_result_saruman)\n",
    "    standard_dev_saruman = saruman_variance**(1/2)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(standard_dev_gandalf, standard_dev_saruman)"
   ]
